          <span>
           Legacy Society
          </span>
         </a>
        </li>
       </ul>
      </li>
      <li class="plain" id="portaltab-administration-level1">
       <a class="hasChildrens" href="https://hias.tamu.edu/administration" title="">
        <span>
         Administration
        </span>
       </a>
       <ul class="globalSectionsLevel1">
        <li class="plain" id="portaltab-hagler-institute-external-advisory-board-level2">
         <a href="https://hias.tamu.edu/administration/hagler-institute-external-advisory-board" title="The Hagler Institute External Advisory Board annually reviews the activities of the Hagler Institute for Advanced Study at Texas A&amp;M University to provide guidance, advice, and recommendations.">
          <span>
           Hagler Institute External Advisory Board
          </span>
         </a>
        </li>
        <li class="plain" id="portaltab-hagler-institute-faculty-advisory-board-level2">
         <a href="https://hias.tamu.edu/administration/hagler-institute-faculty-advisory-board" title="The Hagler Institute Faculty Advisory Board is charged with the responsibility of studying and analyzing the records of nominees for the Hagler Institute Faculty Fellows, assessing their qualifications, and selecting the scholars to be recruited.">
          <span>
           Hagler Institute Faculty Advisory Board
          </span>
         </a>
        </li>
        <li class="plain" id="portaltab-hagler-institute-administrative-council-level2">
         <a href="https://hias.tamu.edu/administration/hagler-institute-administrative-council" title="The Hagler Institute Administrative Council establishes the rules and oversees the operation of the Institute and reviews its progress. The University’s provost selects the Institute’s director.">
          <span>
           Hagler Institute Administrative Council
          </span>
         </a>
        </li>
       </ul>
      </li>
     </ul>
